1
00:00:00,638 --> 00:00:02,490
I guess...

2
00:00:02,490 --> 00:00:04,354
I do like you after all.

3
00:00:04,354 --> 00:00:05,585
What did you do to her!?

4
00:00:05,585 --> 00:00:07,259
You ditch her for a year

5
00:00:07,259 --> 00:00:09,402
and then come back with a girlfriend
and even get yourself engaged.

6
00:00:09,402 --> 00:00:11,615
Don't come back now and
act like her fucking boyfriend!!

7
00:00:11,615 --> 00:00:13,129
I love you after all that's happened.

8
00:00:13,129 --> 00:00:14,811
What a selfish thing to say.

9
00:00:14,811 --> 00:00:16,602
I can't think of any other woman but you.

10
00:00:16,602 --> 00:00:18,384
I can understand why you're hesitating

11
00:00:18,384 --> 00:00:21,730
but I don't think you should
keep things the way they are now.

12
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:22,864
Makino?

13
00:00:27,332 --> 00:00:28,715
Who could it be?

14
00:00:36,599 --> 00:00:40,621
Episode 6: Confession turns Chaotic!

15
00:00:54,852 --> 00:00:59,346
Sorry for dragging you out here
but the walls were too thin in there.

16
00:00:59,346 --> 00:01:02,848
What is it... that you want to tell me?

17
00:01:06,251 --> 00:01:10,902
To you, has the young master
already became your past?

18
00:01:11,709 --> 00:01:13,066
Huh?

19
00:01:13,895 --> 00:01:15,239
Why are you asking me now?

20
00:01:15,239 --> 00:01:18,783
Shortly after the young master
arrived at New York

21
00:01:18,783 --> 00:01:20,989
there was one accident.

22
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:25,553
Triggered by one innocent phrase the
young master said at a certain party.

23
00:01:25,553 --> 00:01:29,182
I never liked the way that ass--oh

24
00:01:29,182 --> 00:01:32,020
I mean our president--does things.

25
00:01:32,020 --> 00:01:34,176
He didn't mean much by it, as always,

26
00:01:34,176 --> 00:01:38,840
but the media took it as words from the next
president and made a huge deal out of it.

27
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:43,714
People interpreted it as uncertainty in
the future, and our stocks plunged.

28
00:01:43,714 --> 00:01:47,291
I can't believe it...
Just by a word from Doumyouji?

29
00:01:47,291 --> 00:01:50,339
The Doumyouji group suddenly faced a crisis

30
00:01:50,339 --> 00:01:53,689
and the only solution was a mass lay off.

31
00:01:54,271 --> 00:01:56,811
Among those laid off was a
Japanese man named Ken Uchida

32
00:01:56,811 --> 00:01:59,746
whom the young master loved like a brother.

33
00:02:00,817 --> 00:02:06,488
The lay off crushed his family
and he struggled to make a living.

34
00:02:07,094 --> 00:02:11,628
One day, Ken Uchida came to see the president

35
00:02:11,628 --> 00:02:15,313
and asked for employment. However

36
00:02:15,974 --> 00:02:18,740
the president could not answer him

37
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:22,062
and losing all hope

38
00:02:29,069 --> 00:02:32,728
he committed suicide in front of
the young master's own eyes.

39
00:02:34,398 --> 00:02:37,870
That's when he began changing.

40
00:02:38,718 --> 00:02:43,958
I think he started realizing that to stand at
the top means to be responsible for the millions

41
00:02:43,958 --> 00:02:48,805
of lives and living that are
involved with the corporate group.

42
00:02:49,882 --> 00:02:53,770
That's why he was so desperate to change:
to bury his feelings for you

43
00:02:53,770 --> 00:02:58,531
and to stand at the top
of the corporate group.

44
00:02:59,007 --> 00:03:05,448
It was during that time that he saw you again,
and shared his time with you again.

45
00:03:05,966 --> 00:03:12,043
He must have no longer been able to
lie to himself about his true feelings.

46
00:03:16,608 --> 00:03:24,979
But... aren't you completely against
Doumyouji and I dating?

47
00:03:24,979 --> 00:03:28,334
I have to return to New York tomorrow as well.

48
00:03:28,334 --> 00:03:29,992
However

49
00:03:29,992 --> 00:03:34,850
Please don't lower your guard just
because the president herself is absent.

50
00:03:35,746 --> 00:03:37,926
The next step has already...

51
00:03:38,192 --> 00:03:39,346
Eh?

52
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:44,361
It's only when the young master is with you

53
00:03:44,361 --> 00:03:46,971
that he acts human.

54
00:03:46,971 --> 00:03:50,630
As someone who will eventually
stand at the top, I wish for him

55
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:52,451
to always be like so.

56
00:03:54,268 --> 00:03:57,197
I hope you understand my meaning.

57
00:04:03,006 --> 00:04:05,138
Ma-ki-no.

58
00:04:07,112 --> 00:04:08,269
What's wrong?

59
00:04:08,993 --> 00:04:10,343
You gave me a call.

60
00:04:12,721 --> 00:04:14,615
That was

61
00:04:14,615 --> 00:04:16,942
Nishida-san, wasn't he?

62
00:04:22,133 --> 00:04:23,645
What's wrong?

63
00:04:24,326 --> 00:04:25,651
Did something happen?

64
00:04:28,744 --> 00:04:29,594
Not really.

65
00:04:32,203 --> 00:04:34,938
Hey, let's go for a drive somewhere right now.

66
00:04:41,878 --> 00:04:43,084
I guess not.

67
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:47,456
I'm sorry.

68
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:52,417
I'm just really confused now.

69
00:04:57,481 --> 00:05:02,116
Will you be more confused?
Now that I do something like this to you?

70
00:05:04,112 --> 00:05:06,938
Hey Sis! It's been a while.

71
00:05:09,771 --> 00:05:13,386
No, I just... need your help.

72
00:05:15,970 --> 00:05:18,740
I'm serious... Please...

73
00:05:26,502 --> 00:05:28,750
And you just left after that?

74
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:31,132
Well...

75
00:05:31,132 --> 00:05:32,764
I guess you can't help it.

76
00:05:32,764 --> 00:05:36,547
Not after hearing about
Doumyouji-san's past like that.

77
00:05:37,559 --> 00:05:40,923
Hey, what are you going to do
for this year's Valentine?

78
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:42,292
Eh?

79
00:05:42,292 --> 00:05:47,850
Maybe this will be a good opportunity for you
to be honest about your feelings once again.

80
00:05:49,026 --> 00:05:50,239
Yeah....

81
00:05:52,601 --> 00:05:56,094
Maybe I should do something
on Valentine's day too.

82
00:06:02,850 --> 00:06:05,659
By the way...

83
00:06:05,659 --> 00:06:08,821
Yuuki, have Nishikado-san ever
let you ride on the back of his motorcycle once?

84
00:06:09,408 --> 00:06:10,760
No. Why?

85
00:06:11,260 --> 00:06:12,860
There's no mistake about it!

86
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:14,694
Mistress!

87
00:06:14,694 --> 00:06:17,643
That seat is... reserved.

88
00:06:19,882 --> 00:06:21,984
What do you mean, reserved?

89
00:06:21,984 --> 00:06:24,535
It means he's only going to let
one special woman sit there.

90
00:06:24,535 --> 00:06:26,832
One special woman?

91
00:06:28,251 --> 00:06:29,620
Now that you mention it...

92
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:31,609
I don't give girls rides.

93
00:06:33,228 --> 00:06:38,636
I wonder if... Nishikado-san has someone
he can't forget or something.

94
00:06:39,413 --> 00:06:43,755
Good question. I'm sure he must have
experienced his first love too.

95
00:06:43,755 --> 00:06:46,284
First love, huh...

96
00:06:47,372 --> 00:06:50,978
I wonder if he still cares about her...

97
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:54,709
You can't give up, Yuuki-chan!

98
00:06:57,745 --> 00:06:59,420
What? You're going back now?

99
00:06:59,875 --> 00:07:02,374
Because the midnight buses are the cheapest.

100
00:07:02,374 --> 00:07:04,502
Call us as soon as anything comes up, okay?

101
00:07:05,581 --> 00:07:08,564
I can get some spending money
by the end of this month, right?

102
00:07:10,669 --> 00:07:13,202
W-What? You can't?

103
00:07:13,202 --> 00:07:15,380
Of course it's possible.

104
00:07:15,380 --> 00:07:19,867
Exactly. Your father is currently famous
as the Man of the Sea right now!

105
00:07:22,940 --> 00:07:24,448
See you later then!

106
00:07:24,448 --> 00:07:27,742
Make sure you lock the doors
and turn off the gas!

107
00:07:29,756 --> 00:07:32,599
Somehow, Mom and Dad seemed
suspicious, didn't they?

108
00:07:32,599 --> 00:07:33,780
Yeah.

109
00:07:35,273 --> 00:07:36,873
Oh, I need to lock the doors.

110
00:07:39,318 --> 00:07:40,390
What?

111
00:07:40,782 --> 00:07:41,877
Uh...

112
00:07:42,797 --> 00:07:45,852
I... ran out of... sugar.

113
00:07:45,852 --> 00:07:49,970
And I'm currently... looking for someone
who could share some sugar with me

114
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:51,688
in the neighborhood.

115
00:07:51,688 --> 00:07:53,971
Huh? Isn't that a little...

116
00:07:53,971 --> 00:07:56,135
What I mean is...

117
00:07:56,135 --> 00:07:59,497
I was trying to make a commoner's food called...
jaga-niku or something.

118
00:07:59,497 --> 00:08:01,486
You mean niku-jaga?

119
00:08:02,034 --> 00:08:04,931
Hey! We were just about to have dinner!
Why don't you eat with us?

120
00:08:04,931 --> 00:08:06,030
Eh?!

121
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:08,249
Please, come in.

122
00:08:08,249 --> 00:08:11,140
Sis, please make jaga-niku.
I want to eat it too!

123
00:08:11,140 --> 00:08:12,689
Like I said, it's niku-jaga.

124
00:08:12,689 --> 00:08:14,707
Oh, that's right!

125
00:08:14,707 --> 00:08:16,832
- Can I borrow your room?
- Eh?

126
00:08:16,832 --> 00:08:19,918
I want to study for as long as possible.

127
00:08:19,918 --> 00:08:22,310
Wait, what are you talking about?
Aren't you already done with your exam?

128
00:08:24,445 --> 00:08:25,540
What are you doing?

129
00:08:26,444 --> 00:08:27,690
O-Oh! That's right!!

130
00:08:27,690 --> 00:08:29,573
What a coincidence. I'm going in!

131
00:08:29,573 --> 00:08:30,573
Hey!

132
00:08:42,069 --> 00:08:48,009
He must have no longer been able to lie
to himself about his true feelings.

133
00:08:57,144 --> 00:08:58,283
What are you...

134
00:09:02,764 --> 00:09:04,437
I'm serious...

135
00:09:05,259 --> 00:09:06,640
about what I said yesterday.

136
00:09:09,664 --> 00:09:10,843
I want to say it again, properly.

137
00:09:11,704 --> 00:09:12,601
Stop!

138
00:09:15,034 --> 00:09:18,416
Where... is your hand right now?

139
00:09:21,198 --> 00:09:23,255
N-N-No, that's not it.

140
00:09:23,255 --> 00:09:25,207
It was an accident--

141
00:09:26,298 --> 00:09:28,605
Get your hand off me now!

142
00:09:46,156 --> 00:09:49,710
Grandpa...! B-Bodies fell... into our room!

143
00:09:49,710 --> 00:09:51,046
Sorry.

144
