167
00:12:05,267 --> 00:12:06,537
Hey, Rui

168
00:12:06,537 --> 00:12:09,539
have you talked to Tsukasa since then?

169
00:12:09,539 --> 00:12:10,653
Nah

170
00:12:10,653 --> 00:12:13,594
Are you seriously serious about Makino?

171
00:12:14,346 --> 00:12:16,755
Who knows?

172
00:12:16,755 --> 00:12:18,979
It's not "who knows?"
What are you gonna do about it?

173
00:12:18,979 --> 00:12:20,539
About what?

174
00:12:21,621 --> 00:12:26,011
But if Tsukasa's feelings are
all going towards Makino

175
00:12:26,011 --> 00:12:29,937
Is he going to break things off
clean with Oogahara Shigeru?

176
00:12:29,937 --> 00:12:33,723
At this rate, I don't think your friendship
with Tsukasa looks too good.

177
00:12:33,723 --> 00:12:37,096
Who cares?
The worst that can happen is...

178
00:12:37,096 --> 00:12:38,591
Rui...

179
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:40,337
Besides

180
00:12:40,337 --> 00:12:44,835
the one who has to make the decision
is neither me nor Tsukasa, right?

181
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,625
It's something Makino needs to decide--

182
00:12:46,625 --> 00:12:48,696
But what about Shizuka?

183
00:12:48,696 --> 00:12:52,685
Huh? Didn't I tell you?

184
00:12:52,685 --> 00:12:55,579
Thank you for everything.

185
00:12:57,619 --> 00:12:59,478
Shizuka and I are over.

186
00:12:59,861 --> 00:13:01,245
No way...

187
00:13:01,245 --> 00:13:02,381
Yes, way.

188
00:13:02,381 --> 00:13:05,772
Hey, hey, did you hear?
That peasant girl's apartment floor fell and

189
00:13:05,772 --> 00:13:08,982
they're going to tear down the whole building!

190
00:13:08,983 --> 00:13:11,332
No way! That's picture-perfect misery!

191
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:16,230
- But the news is bottomlessly pleasant.
- My, that was quite nice, Minako.

192
00:13:17,567 --> 00:13:19,403
Wow wow
Are they serious?

193
00:13:20,085 --> 00:13:24,055
You were with him, right? The one who
bought the entire apartment building from us?

194
00:13:24,055 --> 00:13:26,154
Y-Yes...

195
00:13:26,154 --> 00:13:28,494
Do you know him?

196
00:13:28,987 --> 00:13:31,093
Well, I guess, in a way.

197
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,419
I see.

198
00:13:37,343 --> 00:13:38,378
Oh, here's your change.

199
00:13:39,703 --> 00:13:43,907
Then, do you happen to know his friends too?

200
00:13:44,323 --> 00:13:46,911
- You mean the F4?
- Yes, them.

201
00:13:48,048 --> 00:13:51,012
Yes, I guess you can say... I know them.

202
00:13:52,202 --> 00:13:54,053
I see.

203
00:13:58,703 --> 00:13:59,710
Onee-san!

204
00:13:59,710 --> 00:14:00,584
Long time no see!

205
00:14:00,584 --> 00:14:02,391
I'm not Yomogi, by the way!

206
00:14:02,667 --> 00:14:03,710
Tsukushi-chan.

207
00:14:08,758 --> 00:14:11,047
It smells so good!

208
00:14:13,073 --> 00:14:14,584
All done.

209
00:14:26,125 --> 00:14:28,047
I need to talk to you. Make some time.

210
00:14:38,503 --> 00:14:40,237
Here is fine. Thank you.

211
00:14:40,237 --> 00:14:42,708
Sis! You got here fast!

212
00:14:42,708 --> 00:14:44,775
Tsukasa, I brought you a souvenir.

213
00:14:44,775 --> 00:14:45,997
Thanks.

214
00:14:45,997 --> 00:14:48,111
But before that, Sis,
about what we talked about the other day...

215
00:14:48,111 --> 00:14:49,451
It's all right.

216
00:14:49,451 --> 00:14:51,178
Eh? It's all right? But...

217
00:14:51,178 --> 00:14:53,041
I said it's all right.

218
00:14:55,743 --> 00:14:57,087
Makino!! H-Hi...

219
00:14:57,087 --> 00:14:59,223
What kind of dumb sound is that?

220
00:14:59,223 --> 00:15:01,293
You realize Tsukushi-chan just lost a place to live.

221
00:15:01,293 --> 00:15:04,809
Oh! I was just... thinking about that too.

222
00:15:05,224 --> 00:15:07,373
I have a good idea.

223
00:15:07,373 --> 00:15:09,604
It's really all right. I can't possibly ask you to...

224
00:15:09,604 --> 00:15:12,989
You can! You promised
you'll leave everything up to me, didn't you?

225
00:15:12,989 --> 00:15:15,173
Hey, what happened? What's going on?

226
00:15:15,173 --> 00:15:16,665
Can you believe this idiot

227
00:15:16,665 --> 00:15:18,157
called me to ask me for my help on

228
00:15:18,157 --> 00:15:21,982
how he can break his engagement
and start all over with Makino?

229
00:15:21,982 --> 00:15:24,692
Hey! Don't say such
embarrassing things in front of her!

230
00:15:24,692 --> 00:15:26,881
But it's important!

231
00:15:26,881 --> 00:15:30,019
Tsukasa, there's no lie in
those words of yours, is there?

232
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:35,545
Yeah.

233
00:15:36,365 --> 00:15:38,070
Then it's decided!

234
00:15:38,542 --> 00:15:39,911
Come with me.

235
00:15:41,384 --> 00:15:43,772
- Hey, wait. What's going--
- You stay here and clean that up.

236
00:15:53,290 --> 00:15:55,284
I'll be waiting at the same cafe as last time.
--Shigeru

237
00:16:12,765 --> 00:16:16,109
Don't make a face like that.
Come on in.

238
00:16:16,109 --> 00:16:18,520
You can use this place
anyway you want from today.

239
00:16:19,042 --> 00:16:20,603
Are you serious?

240
00:16:21,327 --> 00:16:24,907
I think you'll be able to hide here
for a while if you're careful.

241
00:16:25,611 --> 00:16:27,042
But...

242
00:16:28,613 --> 00:16:31,481
You don't like... being close to Tsukasa?

243
00:16:33,686 --> 00:16:35,441
T-That's...

244
00:16:38,232 --> 00:16:46,144
If you still think it won't work out, it's okay.
That's a problem between the two of you.

245
00:16:46,797 --> 00:16:51,281
But... I don't want any more people to suffer

246
00:16:51,281 --> 00:16:55,368
because of what my mother has done.

247
00:16:55,368 --> 00:16:56,657
Eh?

248
00:16:58,325 --> 00:17:00,978
When I was in high school,

249
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:04,877
I used to date a boy from
an average working class family too.

250
00:17:04,877 --> 00:17:06,529
YOU too?

